      <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__xasu__lms__common__apis_1ga5424e0629ae8a2da990c72a8aba4b92d" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>s32</type>
        <definition>s32 XAsu_LmsValidateParams</definition>
        <argsstring>(const XAsu_LmsHssSignVerifyParams *LmsParamsPtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XAsu_LmsValidateParams</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="struct_x_asu___lms_hss_sign_verify_params" kindref="compound">XAsu_LmsHssSignVerifyParams</ref> *</type>
          <declname>LmsParamsPtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function validates the LMS signature verification parameters. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>LmsParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_asu___lms_hss_sign_verify_params" kindref="compound">XAsu_LmsHssSignVerifyParams</ref> structure which holds the LMS signature verification parameters.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if validation of LMS parameters is successful.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if any argument is invalid. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Validate LMS params pointer.</para><para>Validate message address.</para><para>Validate signature address and length.</para><para>Validate signature length against NIST SP 800-208 bounds. Minimum: 780 bytes (smallest LMS param set: N=24, W=8, H=5). Maximum: 18708 bytes (largest 2-level HSS: N=32, W=1, H=25).</para><para>Validate that exactly one of PubKeyAddr or PubKeyId is provided.</para><para>Validate public key length is within NIST SP 800-208 valid range. Min: 48 bytes (LMS N=24), Max: 60 bytes (HSS N=32) if PublicKeyAddr is provided.</para><para>Validate PreHashedMsg flag value.</para><para>Validate message length for pre-hashed case per NIST SP 800-208. When message is NOT pre-hashed: any length is valid per RFC 8554. When message IS pre-hashed: length must equal a NIST-valid hash output size (24 bytes for N=24 parameter sets, 32 bytes for N=32 parameter sets).</para><para>Validate message length doesn&apos;t exceed DMA max transfer length.</para><para>Validate SHA type and mode per NIST SP 800-208 / RFC 8554. LMS only permits two hash functions:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>SHA-256: ShaType = XASU_SHA2_TYPE, ShaMode = XASU_SHA_MODE_256</para></listitem><listitem><para>SHAKE256: ShaType = XASU_SHA3_TYPE, ShaMode = XASU_SHA_MODE_SHAKE256 No other combinations (SHA-384, SHA-512, SHA3-256, etc.) are defined in any LMS/HSS parameter set.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/proj/xhdsswstaff1/bhawanas/patch_integration/auto_jobs/esw_github_doxy/git/2026.1/embeddedsw/lib/sw_services/xilasu/src/common/xasu_lms_common.c" line="58" column="1" bodyfile="/proj/xhdsswstaff1/bhawanas/patch_integration/auto_jobs/esw_github_doxy/git/2026.1/embeddedsw/lib/sw_services/xilasu/src/common/xasu_lms_common.c" bodystart="58" bodyend="147"/>
